<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T21:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9347: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T10:00:00+08:00">August 14, 1937—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 14—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>476. My 474, August 13, 10 p.m. Heavy artillery firing still
                                continues same area at intervals. So far as I am able to ascertain
                                all Americans at Shanghai are safe and have withdrawn from areas of
                                firing.</p>
                            <p>2. Chinese City Government functioning just outside of French
                                Concession at Fenglingchao. Sent to the Department, Nanking and
                                Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>